==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: outhouse
<hw>out"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small
house or building at a little distance from the main house; an
outbuilding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Especially</specif>: <def>A small building with
one or more seats and a pit underneath, intended for use as a toilet; a
privy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outing</ent>⟦br⟧
